This paper deals with natural language processing and parsing using neural networks, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of bi-directional LSTM networks suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions achieving state-of-the-art results, which suggests a focus on optimization and performance (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV) may also be relevant if the parsing involves visual information.
